sql:
SELECT stock_id, COUNT(trend_id) AS total_trends
FROM stock_trends
GROUP BY stock_id;

external_knowledge:
Average high and low prices refer to the mean values of the highest and lowest prices of a stock over a certain period of time, respectively; 
Alert counts refer to the number of times a stock triggered a 'price above' or 'price below' alert; 
Average economic indicator value is the mean value of economic indicators associated with a stock over its respective time frame;
Trading signal counts refer to the number of 'buy' and 'sell' signals generated for a stock.

- "Sounded the alarm more than five times" refers to stocks with more than 5 alerts; 
- "Given the green light to buy" refers to trading signals of type 'buy'; 
- "Tidal wave of trading activity" refers to days with trading volume above 1 million shares; 
- "Price oscillations charted between the start and end of last year" means the average high and low prices were calculated for the period from January 1, 2023, to December 31, 2023.
